  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A heterogeneous GNN was developed to improve the prediction of post-marketing adverse drug reactions by learning node representations of a heterogeneous drug-disease graph from 12 years of healthcare claims data (73).",
    "The GNN aggregated the information of each drug/disease node, and the weighted sum of neighboring node features in previous GNN layers were used as node features for subsequent layers.",
    "The performance of the algorithm for predicting drug-ADR pairs was superior to that of a logistic regression model and neural network (AUC = 0.795 vs. 0.631 and 0.739, respectively).",
    "Combining several forms of the algorithm also predicted ADRs not present in the database. 9 Knowledge graphs",
    "A knowledge graph (KG) has been defined as a graph of data intended to accumulate and convey knowledge of the real world, whose nodes represent entities of interest and whose edges represent the different relations between these entities (74)."
  ],
